Former Vice President, Atiku Abubakar has demanded justice for murdered Oluwabamise Ayanwole. Atiku expressed hope that those behind the murder of Ayanwole should be made to face the wrath of the law. In a tweet, the Peoples Democratic Party, PDP, Presidential aspirant, described Ayanwole’s murder as heartbreaking. According to Atiku, the act of taking the life of another human being is despicable. He wrote: “The reports of the murder of 22-year-old Miss Oluwabamise Ayanwole, who went missing on a Lagos Bus Rapid Transit vehicle, is heartbreaking. “The act of taking the life of another human under any circumstance is despicable. I hope that the culprit(s) will be brought to book. “The family, especially the mother, needs all the support and assistance to overcome this tragedy.” The 22-year-old went missing after she boarded a BRT bus in Lagos State. Following alarms raised, her corpse was discovered and the driver of the bus, Nice was arrested. After his arrest, Nice narrated how some passengers abducted the 22-year-old in his bus.